<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr>  However as soon as you realize that you will be leaving a guild...leave. Don't drag it out, hoping for that last bit of loot or the help for your epic. That is simply rude and your negative feelings about a guild will hurt that guild and all of your social relationships in that guild. Save what you can of your reputation, your friends and get out as soon as you know you will be leaving. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
This is the worst for me.  Not to long ago we had some members leave.  It was a very sore subject for a very long time because we had just completed our first cleric epic (the one that left).  The sick part was they knew they were leaving, they planned it in advance, and coincidentally waited untill the cleric epic was complete before disbanding.<br>
<br>
I will never do my epic quest, its no longer a goal for my eq future as I dont ever want anyone thinking of me the way I think of the ones who used me and the Eternal Haven guild.  Thinking back on those members, make me sick.  I wasted so much emotion and time, I gave so freely to them, and was repaid with a knife in my back.   <br>
<br>
Those people arent worth the memory's, laughs, or tears we once shared.  I've been told there is actually a person behind the character.  Sometimes I doubt that, unless some are just born without hearts.<br>
