<br>
However my point here is that I too am an officer in a guild.  It is a smaller guild and we do okay with it, since we have a couple allies as well.  We like to keep it a &quot;family guild&quot; so we can all know each other real well and *hope* that we don't have to worry about any problems with people (not liking one another, loot stealing etc etc).<br>
<br>
Well, about 2 months ago we happened to have a bad Hate raid.  We did break in fine and ran along the wall to the camp site.  We had only one monk with us for pulling, and very unfortunately only 1 chanter and 2 clerics.  We *thought* more were going to show because they said they were going to but never did.  Okay so we have a bad raid, there weren't any wipe-outs or anything, really not that many deaths either!  Only maybe like 4, but we split the loot (gems) after the clerics got their compensations, and port out.  (Btw about a billion shammy and cleric bps dropped with the few mobs we killed lol, which half of them rotted)<br>
<br>
A few days later we notice that &quot;Soandso is no longer part of your guild&quot;.  We start to ask questions and the GL nor the other officer haven't removed anyone.  So the GL /tell's them and asks what's going on.  Well the first to leave was a wizzy who we had JUST finished getting her epic.  She had been in the guild from the beginning, about 9 months, and gave some reasons how the GL was getting sloppy and a whole bunch of other crap.  Our GL did everything for us and you can never expect you GL to do EVERYTHING for you, especially a raid.  It takes GUILD cooperation to succeed.  Well the GL just says, &quot;Okay, bye then.  We don't need you if you have an attitude like that.&quot;<br>
<br>
A few days later more people start to leave because of ONE bad raid, which we didn't even really get to plan because the guild in front of us on the rotation dropped out so we thought we'd just take it.  So no planning.<br>
<br>
So one BS answer, one right after the other is thrown out.  And EVERY single one of them that dropped out went to a guild that, well we don't get along very well with, JUST to piss our GL and the rest of us off.  They stay there for a bit (cause of course we keep track of our ex-guildies) and notice about a month later they are all in different guilds.  One went through 4 guilds in 2 weeks.<br>
<br>
Only advice would be, make SURE you know what you're getting into, with a guild.  Make sure it's what you're looking for and don't let one or two bad inccidents drop all you've had.<br>
<br>
Vespay Twilightkicker<br>
