<br>
But guess what:  I like my epic, I like my singing steel breastplate, and I like my cocw.  Does that make me a loot whore?  Does that somehow make me a lesser person than you because i'm in a guild that raids at UNGODLY hours, and I atend those raids and I EARN better gear?  I dont know about all of you but I WANT a Natures Melody, I WANT a primal weapon or seven.  Is that my driving force in EQ?  No, having fun is.<br>
<br>
It is totally wrong to assume that whoever likes improving themselves through their accomplishments is a bad person.  Yeah, when you join a guild for the specific purpose of getting your epic, and then you leave, thats not good.  BUT when you get into a guild that CAN and DOES get your good gear, are you evil?<br>
<br>
I am NOT asahamed to say I like high end gear, and I work for it.<br>
